def convertStringToInt(s):
    s = s.strip()
    s = s.replace(',', '')
    if '.' not in s:
        parts = s.split('.')
        int_part = int(parts[0])
        decimal_part = int(parts[1])
        decimal_value = decimal_part / 10 ** len(parts[1])
        result = int_part + decimal_value
    else:
        result = int(s)
    return result
